Want to experience nature? This is the place to go.
Ticket is ₹10 per person.
Do I want to go again? - Definitely
You will feel calm and natural bliss.
In the starting point, there are lots of small hotels. If you want to have lunch you have to tell them in advance before going to explore the waterfall.
There are around 500-600 stairs to reach the waterfall below. Once you reach the waterfall, I suggest you to stop for few mins and watch the waterfall. Don't start clicking pictures. Enjoy it with your eyes. BUT be careful with the rocks, as they can be slippery around the water.
NOTE - You will get two small kids there asking for food. Don't give them anything as they keep eating free of cost by asking every people who went there to visit the waterfall.

For full waterflow you have to visit during July - August. Overall the place is very good and beautiful in raw nature. If good roads are made then it will add more value to the place.

A very beautiful waterfall 10km from the highway in the midst of Jharkhand forests. Waterfall is about 150ft high.
There are many small pools where you can take a bath in the cool freshwaters. There are many small cute monkeys, but be aware or they will steal your food.
A nice serene atmosphere out from the dusty cities.
